WEBVTT

00:02.080 --> 00:03.420
Man:
No one expected to arrive

00:03.420 --> 00:04.420
in the water,
beneath the surface.

00:04.420 --> 00:05.960
Previously on "The Crossing"...

00:05.960 --> 00:07.580
Leah:
We were running away.

00:07.580 --> 00:09.420
-Jude: From what?
-The war.

00:09.420 --> 00:11.830
-But there's no war.
-There will be.

00:11.830 --> 00:13.960
We're not the first ones
to comes here.

00:13.960 --> 00:15.290
How long
have you been here?

00:15.290 --> 00:16.500
Longer than you think.

00:16.500 --> 00:18.790
Come on, Marshall,
what did you do now?

00:18.790 --> 00:21.170
I guess you weren't able to
bring anything from home?

00:21.170 --> 00:23.210
This locket,
but I lost it in the ocean.

00:23.210 --> 00:25.000
Caleb: Apex took over
the government.

00:25.000 --> 00:26.790
They hunted us
like animals.

00:26.790 --> 00:29.120
They were genetically engineered
killing machines.

00:29.120 --> 00:30.830
They created a virus.

00:30.830 --> 00:34.290
I just want my daughter.
She can't be away from me.

00:34.290 --> 00:35.920
This is Mantle's Disease.

00:37.460 --> 00:39.330
No!

00:39.330 --> 00:40.540
[ Machine-gun fire ]
-Aaaah!

00:40.540 --> 00:41.790
[ Groans ]

00:46.460 --> 00:48.500
[ Breathing heavily ]

00:48.500 --> 00:53.880
♪♪

00:53.880 --> 00:55.250
[ Breathing quickens ]

01:09.420 --> 01:11.000
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:12.750 --> 01:14.710
Tell me you got an update.

01:14.710 --> 01:16.120
Still no body.

01:16.120 --> 01:19.040
[ Indistinct conversations ]

01:19.040 --> 01:20.750
You said she was hit.

01:20.750 --> 01:23.420
"A likely kill shot."
Your words.

01:23.420 --> 01:25.790
You want to drag the harbor,
Craig, be my guest.

01:25.790 --> 01:28.580
This is Apex. If there's no
body, assume the worst.

01:28.580 --> 01:30.920
You're gonna need more
contractors.

01:30.920 --> 01:33.420
Local emergency calls will be
filtered through intercept.

01:33.420 --> 01:35.920
If anybody sees anything,
we'll be first responders.

01:35.920 --> 01:37.460
We'll go door-to-door
if need be.

01:37.460 --> 01:39.080
Sounds low-profile.

01:39.080 --> 01:41.750
I know what
my job entails.

01:41.750 --> 01:45.290
Unlike you,
I've actually killed them.

01:45.290 --> 01:46.710
Well, that was
a long time ago...

01:48.420 --> 01:49.880
She's alone.

01:49.880 --> 01:51.380
Wounded.

01:51.380 --> 01:53.250
And I've whipped up
a little something

01:53.250 --> 01:55.380
that should give me
an advantage.

01:55.380 --> 01:56.830
Man: All right,
this might be a lead.

01:56.830 --> 01:58.960
Infrared is picking up a heat
signal in the Western Ridge.

01:58.960 --> 02:01.790
♪♪

02:01.790 --> 02:04.380
[ Groans ]

02:04.380 --> 02:07.500
[ Sighs ]

02:07.500 --> 02:08.880
I'm scared.

02:08.880 --> 02:11.460
Hey, what does being
a mommy mean?

02:11.460 --> 02:13.500
That you're always gonna be
there for me.

02:13.500 --> 02:14.620
That's right.

02:18.080 --> 02:20.000
[ Door dings ]

02:20.000 --> 02:26.830
♪♪

02:26.830 --> 02:28.920
[ Clattering ]

02:41.670 --> 02:45.120
♪♪

02:49.540 --> 02:54.000
♪♪

02:58.420 --> 02:59.420
Morning.

02:59.420 --> 03:00.710
Hey, Jude.

03:00.710 --> 03:02.920
Just getting out the toys
for the open house.

03:02.920 --> 03:05.250
Figured it'd be busy with all
the, you know, stuff that's --

03:05.250 --> 03:06.670
Hey!

03:06.670 --> 03:08.960
You must be Oliver.
I heard a lot about you.

03:08.960 --> 03:11.000
Ollie, this is Nestor.

03:11.000 --> 03:14.880
Don't let the beard fool you.
He is in fact an actual deputy.

03:14.880 --> 03:16.500
-It's true.
-Hi.

03:16.500 --> 03:19.830
Hi. You look like you're gonna
be a heck of a sheriff one day,

03:19.830 --> 03:21.170
just like your dad, huh?

03:21.170 --> 03:23.290
I'm not a big fan
of guns.

03:23.290 --> 03:24.210
Oh.

03:26.210 --> 03:29.580
Well, they've got plenty
of other jobs

03:29.580 --> 03:31.500
that don't require
the gun.

03:31.500 --> 03:34.380
Desk jobs and so forth.

03:34.380 --> 03:36.170
Dispatch.
You could do that, you know?

03:36.170 --> 03:37.580
You got to wear that headset
all day,

03:37.580 --> 03:39.330
you're talking into that,
your ear gets sweaty.

03:39.330 --> 03:40.670
It's not the best job
in the world.

03:40.670 --> 03:42.880
Hey, Ollie, there's a bathroom
around the corner.

03:42.880 --> 03:44.330
Why don't you use it
before we go?

03:46.120 --> 03:48.750
Hey, we got to take him
to the range.

03:48.750 --> 03:50.750
Hey, did we get
any calls yesterday

03:50.750 --> 03:53.670
about any suspicious activity
down at the shipyard?

03:54.920 --> 03:57.790
No. I-I saw
in the duty log

03:57.790 --> 04:00.210
that there was some
heavy air traffic.

04:00.210 --> 04:01.540
Figured it was probably
the Air Force

04:01.540 --> 04:03.290
just scrambling some choppers
out of Lewis-McChord.

04:03.290 --> 04:04.460
Probably some kind
of drills.

04:04.460 --> 04:06.170
Hm.

04:06.170 --> 04:09.000
Do me a favor,
if you hear anything,

04:09.000 --> 04:10.710
get any calls,
get me on my cell.

04:10.710 --> 04:12.380
Yes, sir.

04:12.380 --> 04:13.880
Anything you want to
bring me in on?

04:13.880 --> 04:17.330
No, just...

04:17.330 --> 04:19.170
if you get any calls,
let me know.

04:19.170 --> 04:20.170
Yeah.

04:20.170 --> 04:21.830
We'll be at Harborfest.

04:21.830 --> 04:23.830
Yeah, no, yeah.

04:23.830 --> 04:24.960
Have fun.

04:24.960 --> 04:26.750
Yeah,
and kick Marshall.

04:26.750 --> 04:28.290
[ Door clanks ]

04:28.290 --> 04:30.040
All right. Wake up.

04:30.040 --> 04:32.750
I requested
a late checkout.

04:32.750 --> 04:35.880
The guy you got into it with
declined to press charges,

04:35.880 --> 04:37.710
so you're good to go home.

04:37.710 --> 04:39.170
[ Exhales ]

04:39.170 --> 04:41.120
You got to stop doing this,
Marshall.

04:41.120 --> 04:43.920
Come on, these tourists
come for Harborfest,

04:43.920 --> 04:45.830
they blow in like
they own the place.

04:45.830 --> 04:48.040
It's not about
some tourist.

04:49.830 --> 04:53.080
It's 10 years
since the accident.

04:53.080 --> 04:54.830
And I am sorry,

04:54.830 --> 04:56.830
but you can't keep
living in the past.

04:56.830 --> 04:58.960
You have to start
thinking about your future.

04:58.960 --> 05:03.830
♪♪

05:03.830 --> 05:06.080
Maybe I don't have one.

05:12.920 --> 05:13.960
[ Door closes ]

05:13.960 --> 05:16.210
[ Breathing heavily ]

05:16.210 --> 05:19.920
Who else knows
about the earlier migration?

05:19.920 --> 05:21.460
[ Sighs ] No one.

05:26.290 --> 05:28.250
You don't have to do this.

05:28.250 --> 05:30.920
I'm not gonna tell anyone.

05:30.920 --> 05:34.500
You need to understand
that here, in this time,

05:34.500 --> 05:36.040
you have no power.

05:36.040 --> 05:37.920
You have no freedom.

05:37.920 --> 05:41.670
You have no life,
except the one I give you.

05:41.670 --> 05:43.830
I understand.

05:43.830 --> 05:45.250
Good.

05:45.250 --> 05:48.670
Then maybe you can
be of use to us.

05:48.670 --> 05:51.420
♪♪

05:51.420 --> 05:55.540
Thomas: The best thing
is just to be patient.

05:55.540 --> 05:57.250
The guy I talked to?

05:57.250 --> 05:59.330
He said talking about
where we're from

05:59.330 --> 06:00.920
is not helping our cause.

06:00.920 --> 06:03.080
They think we're crazy.

06:03.080 --> 06:06.420
And they don't let crazy people
just walk around...

06:06.420 --> 06:09.380
Crazy people get locked up.

06:09.380 --> 06:11.750
[ Hushed voice ]
Hey, what's this?

06:11.750 --> 06:14.170
[ Hushed voice ] He was out
of the camp yesterday.

06:14.170 --> 06:15.710
He talked
with someone in charge.

06:15.710 --> 06:17.210
They're ready to help.

06:17.210 --> 06:20.210
There's money available to us,
places to live, even jobs.

06:20.210 --> 06:22.120
Did you see
these places?

06:22.120 --> 06:24.790
Just pictures.

06:24.790 --> 06:29.000
If you want a life here,
do exactly what they tell you,

06:29.000 --> 06:30.790
and say as little
as possible.

06:30.790 --> 06:32.830
[ Crowd murmuring ]

06:32.830 --> 06:37.670
♪♪

06:37.670 --> 06:42.210
♪♪

06:42.210 --> 06:46.790
♪♪

06:46.790 --> 06:52.170
♪♪

06:52.170 --> 06:54.880
Where'd you get those?

06:54.880 --> 06:56.920
Oh, I found them.

06:56.920 --> 07:00.290
♪♪

07:00.290 --> 07:02.380
Yeah, well, they don't
hide who you are,

07:02.380 --> 07:04.750
if that's what
you were hoping.

07:04.750 --> 07:06.120
Do I know you?

07:08.420 --> 07:10.540
No, but I know you.

07:12.080 --> 07:14.960
And I know what you did
back in Metolius.

07:17.460 --> 07:19.500
[ Hushed voice ] If these
settlers found out,

07:19.500 --> 07:24.210
I don't even want to think
about what they'd do to you.

07:26.420 --> 07:28.580
But...

07:30.580 --> 07:33.000
maybe we can work something
out...

07:36.920 --> 07:39.250
...so that doesn't happen.

07:39.250 --> 07:42.210
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:51.830 --> 07:54.120
[ Indistinct conversations ]

07:55.920 --> 07:57.750
Hi, Roy.

07:57.750 --> 07:59.330
Hey.
What's going on?

08:01.920 --> 08:03.580
Can I ask you something?

08:03.580 --> 08:06.540
Do you know how long
we're gonna be here?

08:06.540 --> 08:09.380
I'm not a part
of those conversations.

08:09.380 --> 08:11.250
But I meant what I said,
if there's anything

08:11.250 --> 08:13.250
I could do for you to make
things a little easier --

08:13.250 --> 08:14.580
You could get me
out of here.

08:14.580 --> 08:17.920
♪♪

08:17.920 --> 08:20.420
I can't do that, Hannah.

08:20.420 --> 08:22.750
That would be
breaking the law.

08:22.750 --> 08:24.420
There are
serious penalties.

08:24.420 --> 08:26.500
Yeah, it's okay.
I understand.

08:26.500 --> 08:29.670
♪♪

08:29.670 --> 08:32.250
Is there anything else
going on?

08:32.250 --> 08:33.710
No.

08:33.710 --> 08:35.380
No, it's fine.

08:35.380 --> 08:37.080
I just --
I shouldn't have asked.

08:37.080 --> 08:40.960
♪♪

08:40.960 --> 08:42.420
[ Door opens ]

08:44.540 --> 08:46.710
Hey, hey.

08:46.710 --> 08:49.620
All right, here it is.

08:49.620 --> 08:51.880
[ Classic rock music playing ]

08:51.880 --> 08:55.790
All right, this is it.

08:55.790 --> 08:57.620
What do you think?

08:57.620 --> 08:58.880
What is it?

08:58.880 --> 09:01.710
Harborfest.
It's a tradition.

09:03.170 --> 09:05.170
Come on, man.
It's gonna be fun.

09:05.170 --> 09:07.380
There's, like,
games and music.

09:07.380 --> 09:09.960
There's a guy who juggles
salmon...

09:09.960 --> 09:13.120
and all kinds
of junk food.

09:13.120 --> 09:14.830
Don't tell your mom.

09:14.830 --> 09:17.250
I thought we were
gonna go fishing.

09:17.250 --> 09:18.750
Just you and me.
-Yeah, we are.

09:18.750 --> 09:21.040
I just thought I'd show
you the town first.

09:23.170 --> 09:25.250
So...

09:25.250 --> 09:27.040
what kind of junk food?

09:27.040 --> 09:28.790
[ Chuckles ]
Yeah, now we're talkin'!

09:28.790 --> 09:30.040
Come on, let's go.

09:30.040 --> 09:32.330
[ Up-tempo music playing ]

09:32.330 --> 09:38.380
♪♪

09:38.380 --> 09:40.000
Do you think
she'll like it?

09:40.000 --> 09:42.250
Oliver: Dad.

09:42.250 --> 09:44.120
Yeah, I'm coming.

10:05.080 --> 10:08.080
[ Whooshing ]

10:16.500 --> 10:19.250
The trail is taking her back
toward the town.

10:19.250 --> 10:22.040
If she gets to
the general population,

10:22.040 --> 10:23.750
this becomes
a lot more difficult.

10:23.750 --> 10:27.500
So we're gonna stay
south by southwest.

10:27.500 --> 10:29.670
So keep her cordoned off.

10:29.670 --> 10:33.420
Amount of blood she's lost,
she's lucky to be on her feet.

10:33.420 --> 10:35.670
You underestimate
this target,

10:35.670 --> 10:38.170
she will be the last thing
you see on this earth.

10:40.290 --> 10:41.960
Move out.

10:43.500 --> 10:49.120
♪♪

10:49.120 --> 10:55.500
♪♪

10:57.790 --> 10:59.210
You really punching out?

10:59.210 --> 11:01.670
[ Whistles ] There goes
your double overtime,

11:01.670 --> 11:02.830
just floating away.

11:02.830 --> 11:05.710
Yeah, heading back
to the hotel.

11:05.710 --> 11:09.290
If I don't get some sleep,
I'll be useless.

11:09.290 --> 11:11.290
What use are you now?

11:11.290 --> 11:12.540
This isn't
exactly Guantanamo.

11:12.540 --> 11:14.380
Give these kooks
some colored pencils,

11:14.380 --> 11:15.750
and they take care
of themselves.

11:15.750 --> 11:17.920
Hell, I'll take
all the shifts.

11:19.210 --> 11:21.170
You're a real patriot.

11:21.170 --> 11:25.920
[ Upbeat country music plays ]

11:25.920 --> 11:27.620
[ Whistle blows ]

11:28.750 --> 11:30.500
[ Brakes squeal ]

11:30.500 --> 11:33.920
♪♪

11:33.920 --> 11:36.330
Come on.

11:36.330 --> 11:38.250
What is this?

11:38.250 --> 11:40.880
[ Music continues ]

11:45.460 --> 11:51.420
♪♪

11:51.420 --> 11:58.170
♪♪

11:58.170 --> 11:59.790
[ Exhales ]

11:59.790 --> 12:01.620
♪♪

12:01.620 --> 12:07.920
[ Whistle blows ]

12:11.670 --> 12:17.710
♪♪

12:17.710 --> 12:21.420
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

12:21.420 --> 12:22.500
Hey.

12:22.500 --> 12:24.120
Emma, hi.
How's the girl?

12:24.120 --> 12:25.710
Not good.
High-grade fever,

12:25.710 --> 12:28.290
fatigue, some respiratory
distress.

12:28.290 --> 12:29.920
I'm sending in
a specialist.

12:29.920 --> 12:31.210
She's gonna develop a screen,

12:31.210 --> 12:32.750
make sure we don't
have more carriers.

12:32.750 --> 12:34.460
I got ahold of the Sheriff.

12:34.460 --> 12:36.830
He wasn't too happy.
I can't say I blame him.

12:36.830 --> 12:38.420
I expect
he'll fall into line.

12:38.420 --> 12:39.750
I reported on his location

12:39.750 --> 12:42.080
because I thought you were gonna
give me the leeway

12:42.080 --> 12:43.620
to meet with him alone.

12:43.620 --> 12:47.420
No, you reported on his location
because it's your job.

12:47.420 --> 12:49.290
Is there something
you aren't telling me?

12:49.290 --> 12:51.120
I told you
I didn't want him involved.

12:51.120 --> 12:52.920
You had to go
and "make him an asset."

12:52.920 --> 12:56.000
So I dealt with the situation.
I made the call.

12:56.000 --> 12:58.790
And do your job or I'll find
someone else to do it.

12:58.790 --> 13:01.120
[ Cellphone clicks ]

13:01.120 --> 13:04.790
If we do exactly what they say,
take care of ourselves,

13:04.790 --> 13:06.960
you know, don't say anything
about what's going on here,

13:06.960 --> 13:08.790
what happened before,
where we came from...

13:08.790 --> 13:10.790
[ Siren wails ]

13:10.790 --> 13:12.170
Sophie: Director Lindauer.

13:12.170 --> 13:15.210
Good morning.
Sir, I'm Dr. Sophie Forbin.

13:15.210 --> 13:16.960
I appreciate you
meeting me in person.

13:16.960 --> 13:19.380
My specialty is
quarantine measurements,

13:19.380 --> 13:21.540
screening methodology,
vaccine production.

13:21.540 --> 13:25.420
If HSI needs a virologist,
I'm eminently qualified.

13:25.420 --> 13:31.380
♪♪

13:31.380 --> 13:34.210
[ Indistinct conversations ]

13:36.040 --> 13:38.920
Director Lindauer.
I'm Dr. Forbin.

13:40.620 --> 13:45.040
Your paper in the Journal
of Microbiotic Virology.

13:45.040 --> 13:46.420
Nice work.

13:46.420 --> 13:48.330
Shall we?

13:48.330 --> 13:50.750
I was one of six co-authors
on that paper.

13:50.750 --> 13:53.750
My sources tell me you did
the bulk of the research.

13:53.750 --> 13:56.210
Anyway, let's skip
your curriculum vitae.

13:56.210 --> 13:58.880
You've been vetted,
I'm impressed.

13:58.880 --> 14:02.580
May I ask what, if anything,
you've heard about Thorn Beach.

14:04.120 --> 14:06.670
The shipwreck?
Only what I saw on the news.

14:06.670 --> 14:08.460
Dozens of fatalities.

14:08.460 --> 14:11.830
And 47 survivors.
English-speaking, coherent --

14:11.830 --> 14:14.830
though they seem to be victims
of some mass delusion.

14:14.830 --> 14:16.330
Brainwashing, perhaps?

14:16.330 --> 14:18.250
Trust me,
you'll understand

14:18.250 --> 14:20.250
when you hear where they claim
to have come from.

14:21.540 --> 14:23.460
What does that have to do
with me?

14:23.460 --> 14:25.250
One of them's displaying
symptoms

14:25.250 --> 14:27.000
of an unidentified virus --
A little girl.

14:27.000 --> 14:28.080
She's dying.

14:28.080 --> 14:29.620
Has she been isolated?

14:29.620 --> 14:32.250
Yes. I need you to prepare
a diagnostic,

14:32.250 --> 14:34.120
see if anyone else
has been infected.

14:34.120 --> 14:35.670
[ Helicopter blades whirring ]

14:35.670 --> 14:38.080
You need me
to stop an outbreak?

14:38.080 --> 14:40.670
I need
your utmost discretion.

14:40.670 --> 14:44.250
You report only to me until we
know more about this thing.

14:44.250 --> 14:45.580
I don't want to start
a panic.

14:45.580 --> 14:46.710
Absolutely.

14:46.710 --> 14:48.960
When do I start?

14:48.960 --> 14:51.620
You just did.

14:54.670 --> 15:00.710
♪♪

15:00.710 --> 15:02.380
[ Exhales ]

15:02.380 --> 15:08.620
♪♪

15:08.620 --> 15:15.080
♪♪

15:15.080 --> 15:16.880
[ Stick cracks ]

15:16.880 --> 15:22.620
♪♪

15:22.620 --> 15:28.580
♪♪

15:28.580 --> 15:35.380
♪♪

15:35.380 --> 15:37.830
Baker team. Stand by.
I think I got something.

15:39.790 --> 15:40.830
[ Groans ]

15:40.830 --> 15:42.670
Myers, sound off.

15:42.670 --> 15:44.250
Where is my daughter?

15:44.250 --> 15:47.000
♪♪

15:47.000 --> 15:48.460
-Myers.
-[ Chokes ]

15:48.460 --> 15:52.210
[ Indistinct conversations ]

15:52.210 --> 15:59.120
♪♪

15:59.120 --> 16:01.620
I'll take it from here.

16:01.620 --> 16:03.380
Dr. Forbin.

16:03.380 --> 16:04.830
Emma Ren.

16:04.830 --> 16:06.500
Sophie, please.

16:06.500 --> 16:08.330
Shouldn't these people
be in quarantine?

16:08.330 --> 16:10.290
We believe we isolated
the patient

16:10.290 --> 16:11.960
before she became
contagious.

16:11.960 --> 16:13.500
How could you know that?

16:13.500 --> 16:16.620
These people have experience
with the virus.

16:16.620 --> 16:20.210
I was told this was an
unidentified pathogen.

16:20.210 --> 16:21.710
It's complicated.

16:21.710 --> 16:24.330
Look, if you want answers,
I'll get them for you.

16:24.330 --> 16:26.420
Whatever it takes
to help this little girl.

16:26.420 --> 16:29.500
Agent Ren, I reviewed
the patient's lab work.

16:29.500 --> 16:32.290
I've never seen this kind of
rapid onset before.

16:32.290 --> 16:35.330
She's experiencing acute
distress, prostration,

16:35.330 --> 16:38.080
exanthema, early signs
of brain inflammation,

16:38.080 --> 16:40.290
and I don't know
how it's transmitted.

16:40.290 --> 16:41.500
Forgive me
if I sound harsh,

16:41.500 --> 16:43.750
but I wasn't brought in here
to save a little girl.

16:43.750 --> 16:46.420
I'm here to prevent
a pandemic.

16:46.420 --> 16:50.460
This Thorn Beach thing
is crazy, right?

16:50.460 --> 16:52.460
The story is
they were all dead,

16:52.460 --> 16:54.500
but Kara's brother
works for the Coast Guard,

16:54.500 --> 16:56.330
and he said that they
pulled a bunch of people

16:56.330 --> 16:58.670
out of the water...
alive.

16:58.670 --> 17:01.120
What the hell
do you think is going on?

17:01.120 --> 17:03.790
Well, in the words of
my great-grandpa Lonny --

17:03.790 --> 17:06.920
if you can't do anything about
it, don't worry about it.

17:06.920 --> 17:11.420
[ Diamond Rings' "Runaway Love"
plays ]

17:11.420 --> 17:12.790
What the hell is this?

17:12.790 --> 17:15.080
♪♪

17:15.080 --> 17:17.880
It's a...
Nerf basketball hoop.

17:17.880 --> 17:19.710
It's an earring, Marshall.

17:19.710 --> 17:21.670
Is it?

17:21.670 --> 17:23.000
Who was here last night?

17:23.000 --> 17:24.960
No one.

17:24.960 --> 17:27.620
♪ I wanna wake up
in a different city ♪

17:27.620 --> 17:28.830
Go to hell.

17:28.830 --> 17:30.500
[ Door slams ]

17:30.500 --> 17:33.170
[ Fiddle playing ]

17:33.170 --> 17:35.420
[ Indistinct conversations ]

17:35.420 --> 17:40.420
♪♪

17:40.420 --> 17:43.790
There you go.
All right, remember.

17:43.790 --> 17:46.210
Be the ball.

17:46.210 --> 17:48.500
Dad, what does that
even mean?

17:48.500 --> 17:50.210
It doesn't have to mean
anything.

17:50.210 --> 17:52.170
It's "Caddyshack."
Now come on, focus.

17:52.170 --> 17:53.330
Be the ball.

17:55.210 --> 17:56.380
Ah, close.

17:56.380 --> 17:57.540
So close. So close.

17:57.540 --> 17:59.540
We're gonna have to
try that one again.

17:59.540 --> 18:01.920
This time, skip
the weighted bottles.

18:01.920 --> 18:04.670
Loosen up.
You got to loosen up.

18:04.670 --> 18:06.580
Way too tight.
Got it?

18:06.580 --> 18:09.420
Okay, focus.

18:09.420 --> 18:11.120
You got it. Do it.

18:12.540 --> 18:15.330
Yeah! What?
Are you kidding me?

18:15.330 --> 18:17.170
[ Chuckles ] Yeah.
What do we get?

18:17.170 --> 18:18.920
What do we get?
-The gray shark.

18:18.920 --> 18:20.920
Of course. Nice!

18:20.920 --> 18:23.170
It was so close.

18:23.170 --> 18:25.000
Thank you.

18:25.000 --> 18:28.040
Nice job!

18:28.040 --> 18:30.750
[ Indistinct conversations ]

18:30.750 --> 18:36.080
♪♪

18:36.080 --> 18:41.380
♪♪

18:41.380 --> 18:47.380
♪♪

18:47.380 --> 18:49.040
[ Chuckles ]

18:49.040 --> 18:52.670
♪♪

18:52.670 --> 18:55.710
Excuse me, is there transport?
Is there --

18:55.710 --> 18:59.540
♪♪

18:59.540 --> 19:03.500
♪♪

19:03.500 --> 19:08.040
♪♪

19:08.040 --> 19:12.460
♪♪

19:12.460 --> 19:14.000
[ Screaming ]

19:15.580 --> 19:19.880
♪♪

19:19.880 --> 19:24.460
♪♪

19:24.460 --> 19:29.290
♪♪

19:33.170 --> 19:38.880
♪♪

19:38.880 --> 19:40.080
Hi.

19:40.080 --> 19:41.120
Yeah?

19:42.830 --> 19:44.920
I was wondering
if you could help me.

19:46.750 --> 19:48.460
With what?

19:48.460 --> 19:51.120
I don't really know
this place.

19:51.120 --> 19:53.620
You lose your tour group
or something?

19:53.620 --> 19:55.670
Yeah.

19:55.670 --> 19:58.210
Maybe you could
show me around?

19:59.710 --> 20:01.750
Private tour's
gonna cost you.

20:01.750 --> 20:03.710
I don't have any money.

20:03.710 --> 20:05.920
-It was a joke.
-Oh.

20:05.920 --> 20:08.250
[ Chuckles ]

20:08.250 --> 20:13.880
♪♪

20:13.880 --> 20:15.290
You hungry?

20:15.290 --> 20:18.420
♪♪

20:18.420 --> 20:21.120
[ Indistinct conversations ]

20:21.120 --> 20:22.500
Here.

20:30.880 --> 20:32.460
Wow.

20:32.460 --> 20:34.080
That's amazing.

20:34.080 --> 20:38.580
So, uh,
where you from anyway?

20:38.580 --> 20:40.790
[ Guitar soloing ]

20:40.790 --> 20:44.920
Um...it's called Metolius.

20:44.920 --> 20:48.040
Yeah? I went river rafting
out there once.

20:48.040 --> 20:50.540
There's like 12 people
in that town.

20:50.540 --> 20:52.670
It's growing.

20:52.670 --> 20:55.420
Where are you from?

20:55.420 --> 20:57.040
Right here.

20:57.040 --> 20:59.540
I'm gonna leave soon,
go to L.A.

20:59.540 --> 21:00.960
It's time.

21:00.960 --> 21:03.040
I don't think
you should do that.

21:03.040 --> 21:05.250
[ Chuckling ] And why not?

21:05.250 --> 21:07.540
Maybe you're meant
to be here.

21:07.540 --> 21:09.880
Man: Are you ready to rock,
Port Canaan?

21:09.880 --> 21:11.420
[ Cheers and applause ]

21:11.420 --> 21:12.670
One, two, three, four.

21:12.670 --> 21:15.040
[ Upbeat country music plays ]

21:15.040 --> 21:16.790
There's so much
music here.

21:16.790 --> 21:20.460
♪♪

21:20.460 --> 21:22.040
Okay.

21:23.420 --> 21:25.500
[ Door opens ]

21:25.500 --> 21:27.830
[ Door closes ]

21:27.830 --> 21:29.080
You wanted to see me?

21:29.080 --> 21:31.290
Hey, Thomas.

21:31.290 --> 21:33.040
Have a seat.

21:37.420 --> 21:41.040
So how was your visit with
my colleague, Mr. Lindauer?

21:41.040 --> 21:43.420
It was good.
Nice guy.

21:43.420 --> 21:45.880
Sounds like the conversation
you and he had

21:45.880 --> 21:48.080
was different from the
conversation you and I had.

21:48.080 --> 21:50.960
Yeah.
I'm sorry I lied to you.

21:50.960 --> 21:52.620
There's no excuse.

21:52.620 --> 21:55.880
It's okay.
Everybody makes mistakes.

21:55.880 --> 21:58.710
But just so I'm clear --

21:58.710 --> 22:02.880
what you told me about
the earlier migration...

22:02.880 --> 22:04.420
that was a lie?

22:04.420 --> 22:05.880
Yes.

22:05.880 --> 22:07.540
That's a pretty
unusual one.

22:07.540 --> 22:09.460
I was trying
to get attention.

22:09.460 --> 22:11.290
I was scared.

22:11.290 --> 22:13.420
You were scared of what?

22:13.420 --> 22:16.290
You know, this --
this whole situation.

22:16.290 --> 22:18.790
I wanted to feel
important.

22:18.790 --> 22:23.580
Which is it? You were scared
or you wanted to feel important?

22:23.580 --> 22:26.880
♪♪

22:26.880 --> 22:30.500
Uh...both.

22:30.500 --> 22:32.830
Jude: Now, who wants to be
my next deputy?

22:32.830 --> 22:34.040
[ All shouting ]

22:34.040 --> 22:36.540
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

22:36.540 --> 22:38.460
All right, all right,
all right, all right.

22:38.460 --> 22:40.670
Hey, it's not all blasting
sirens and chasing bad guys.

22:40.670 --> 22:42.920
Although we do that.
But you know what?

22:42.920 --> 22:45.880
You're gonna have to take
a pledge to protect and serve,

22:45.880 --> 22:49.790
and then you get a badge
and some cool toys.

22:49.790 --> 22:50.670
So who's in?

22:50.670 --> 22:53.250
Together: Me!

22:53.250 --> 22:55.830
All right, wait.
We'll get one right here.

22:55.830 --> 22:57.790
All right, here you go.

22:57.790 --> 22:59.330
Hey, Dad,
can I wear your hat?

22:59.330 --> 23:00.710
Oh.

23:00.710 --> 23:02.500
There you go.

23:02.500 --> 23:06.000
Girl: Can I have one?

23:06.000 --> 23:07.330
[ Exhales ] All right.

23:07.330 --> 23:09.290
Hey, take over
for a second, will you?

23:09.290 --> 23:10.580
Excuse me.

23:12.460 --> 23:13.710
What do you want?

23:13.710 --> 23:15.580
Is there somewhere
we can talk?

23:15.580 --> 23:18.170
I'm sorry, you're too old
to be a junior deputy.

23:18.170 --> 23:19.750
Look, dude...

23:19.750 --> 23:22.040
I think
it's happened before.

23:22.040 --> 23:23.210
What?

23:23.210 --> 23:26.460
There was an earlier migration
of refugees.

23:26.460 --> 23:29.120
-When?
-I don't know.

23:29.120 --> 23:31.040
But I know there's some people
at high levels that do.

23:31.040 --> 23:32.960
The same people that dropped
a Blackwater convention

23:32.960 --> 23:34.040
on the shipyards,
I suppose.

23:34.040 --> 23:35.330
-Yes.
-Yeah.

23:35.330 --> 23:37.000
Why are you coming
to me with this?

23:39.170 --> 23:40.620
You're the only person
I can trust.

23:40.620 --> 23:42.540
[ Scoffs ] Wow.

23:42.540 --> 23:44.790
Listen, if there were others,
they left a trace.

23:44.790 --> 23:46.540
Witnesses. Something.

23:46.540 --> 23:48.170
[ Hushed voice ]
If you went into town

23:48.170 --> 23:49.750
and checked the records --
-No, I can't help you.

23:49.750 --> 23:51.040
This is important.

23:51.040 --> 23:54.250
Hey, you got a boss
who's keeping secrets,

23:54.250 --> 23:56.170
corruption at the top --
Been there.

23:56.170 --> 23:57.750
No desire to go back.

23:59.250 --> 24:02.250
Someone
see Agent Ren out.

24:02.250 --> 24:04.920
Hi, Leah. It's okay.

24:04.920 --> 24:07.380
I'm a doctor.
My name is Sophie.

24:07.380 --> 24:10.620
I have a real important
question to ask.

24:11.960 --> 24:13.790
Do I look stupid
in this suit?

24:14.960 --> 24:16.960
I know I do.

24:16.960 --> 24:19.120
It's so hot as well.

24:19.120 --> 24:21.750
Do you mind?

24:21.750 --> 24:24.750
You know, I was studying
your blood work,

24:24.750 --> 24:27.540
and I saw something
that surprised me.

24:27.540 --> 24:30.460
The way your body is
reacting to the virus,

24:30.460 --> 24:32.920
it's like
it's already fought it.

24:32.920 --> 24:35.710
Have your received treatment
for these symptoms before?

24:35.710 --> 24:37.920
From my mom.

24:37.920 --> 24:39.920
Your mother
gave you medicine?

24:39.920 --> 24:42.620
She was the medicine.

24:42.620 --> 24:48.250
♪♪

24:48.250 --> 24:50.670
[ Sinister music plays ]

24:50.670 --> 24:54.830
♪♪

24:54.830 --> 24:59.040
♪♪

24:59.040 --> 25:03.830
♪♪

25:05.290 --> 25:08.380
[ Both groaning ]

25:08.380 --> 25:09.670
Agh!

25:09.670 --> 25:11.420
[ Groaning ]

25:11.420 --> 25:14.330
[ Grunts ]

25:14.330 --> 25:18.790
[ Groans ]

25:18.790 --> 25:20.540
[ Groans ]

25:22.830 --> 25:23.830
Ahh!

25:23.830 --> 25:27.330
[ Grunting ]

25:29.920 --> 25:31.500
Are you in charge?

25:31.500 --> 25:32.830
N-No.

25:32.830 --> 25:35.290
He's back with the vehicles.

25:35.290 --> 25:37.120
[ Groans ]

25:43.540 --> 25:45.880
[ Birds chirping ]

25:50.120 --> 25:52.330
Excuse me.
Are you Rebecca?

25:52.330 --> 25:55.000
Leah was staying
with you, right?

25:55.000 --> 25:57.080
I'd like to ask you
some questions.

25:57.080 --> 25:58.880
You're wasting your time.

25:58.880 --> 26:01.080
She can't be saved.

26:01.080 --> 26:03.420
That's what I thought at first.
Now I'm not so sure.

26:05.670 --> 26:08.250
Look, I don't know who you
people are, and I don't care.

26:08.250 --> 26:10.420
But if you have insight
into this virus,

26:10.420 --> 26:11.710
you have to talk to me.

26:11.710 --> 26:14.120
That little girl is in there
fighting for her life.

26:15.920 --> 26:17.380
What do you want to know?

26:17.380 --> 26:19.250
I think she's fought this
before,

26:19.250 --> 26:21.540
aided by some type
of treatment, an antiviral.

26:21.540 --> 26:23.540
-There's no treatment.
-She said her mother

26:23.540 --> 26:25.420
used to give her medicine,
made by her blood.

26:25.420 --> 26:27.210
The way Leah talks
about it,

26:27.210 --> 26:29.210
it sounds like her mother
was immune.

26:29.210 --> 26:31.040
No one is immune.
Only...

26:31.040 --> 26:33.040
Only what?

26:35.670 --> 26:36.960
She's a sick little girl.

26:36.960 --> 26:39.040
She doesn't know what
she's talking about.

26:39.040 --> 26:40.710
If you know something,
please tell me.

26:40.710 --> 26:45.290
♪♪

26:45.290 --> 26:48.580
[ Indistinct conversations ]

26:48.580 --> 26:53.580
♪♪

26:53.580 --> 26:58.620
♪♪

26:58.620 --> 27:03.960
♪♪

27:03.960 --> 27:06.790
I have to tell you,
they were very nice.

27:06.790 --> 27:08.790
They showed me around.

27:08.790 --> 27:12.960
I had this sweet liquid
made of combined fruit.

27:12.960 --> 27:14.830
They call it a smoothie.

27:14.830 --> 27:16.540
[ Both chuckle ]

27:16.540 --> 27:20.290
And more importantly,
I established some contacts.

27:20.290 --> 27:21.670
For the outside.

27:21.670 --> 27:25.080
You know, to have a head start
once we get out of here.

27:25.080 --> 27:27.080
That's amazing.

27:35.330 --> 27:39.040
Tell you what,
let's stay in contact.

27:39.040 --> 27:40.420
Happy to help.

27:40.420 --> 27:42.040
Okay.

27:48.080 --> 27:49.750
Hey,
tell me something.

27:49.750 --> 27:53.120
Did they -- they tell you
how long we'd be in this camp?

27:53.120 --> 27:55.080
A couple weeks.

27:55.080 --> 27:56.670
Really?

27:56.670 --> 27:58.710
'Cause I just saw them
unloading

27:58.710 --> 28:00.750
a couple months' worth
of food out front.

28:00.750 --> 28:03.120
The men I talked to
said we'd be out soon.

28:03.120 --> 28:04.920
I took that to mean
a couple weeks.

28:04.920 --> 28:07.710
Huh. I thought you
talked to just one man

28:07.710 --> 28:09.080
in a windowless room.

28:11.420 --> 28:13.420
I got to explain myself
to you?

28:13.420 --> 28:14.580
I'm just asking.

28:14.580 --> 28:16.670
And I answered
your question.

28:16.670 --> 28:19.420
♪♪

28:19.420 --> 28:21.580
You want to go looking
for problems?

28:21.580 --> 28:23.380
I'm sure
you'll find them.

28:23.380 --> 28:26.170
But I guarantee you'll be
the last guy out of this camp,

28:26.170 --> 28:28.170
if at all.

28:28.170 --> 28:32.670
♪♪

28:32.670 --> 28:37.460
♪♪

28:55.170 --> 28:57.790
[ Upbeat country music plays ]

28:57.790 --> 29:03.330
♪♪

29:03.330 --> 29:09.540
♪♪

29:09.540 --> 29:11.880
[ Cheers and applause ]

29:11.880 --> 29:14.210
Man:
We love you, Port Canaan!

29:14.210 --> 29:15.750
Whoo!

29:15.750 --> 29:17.620
[ Chuckles ]

29:17.620 --> 29:19.750
I've never heard
a band like that.

29:19.750 --> 29:22.000
Yeah, they're okay.

29:22.000 --> 29:24.250
I mean, I don't think the Stones
are real worried.

29:24.250 --> 29:25.620
Stones?

29:25.620 --> 29:27.040
[ Scoffs ]

29:27.040 --> 29:28.710
You need to get out more.

29:28.710 --> 29:30.460
Maybe you can take me.

29:33.290 --> 29:35.920
Y'know, you should be
more careful.

29:35.920 --> 29:37.500
What do you mean?

29:37.500 --> 29:39.380
A girl
who looks like you?

29:39.380 --> 29:41.000
You shouldn't trust
someone like me.

29:41.000 --> 29:43.210
Some random guy
you just met in a crowd.

29:43.210 --> 29:47.170
♪♪

29:47.170 --> 29:49.250
You're more than that.

29:49.250 --> 29:51.920
I was meant to find you.

29:51.920 --> 29:54.330
♪♪

29:54.330 --> 29:57.830
They said you were a good man,
someone I could trust.

29:57.830 --> 30:00.080
They said if I found you
I'd be okay.

30:00.080 --> 30:01.960
Is this a joke?

30:01.960 --> 30:03.960
Are you kidding me?

30:03.960 --> 30:07.540
Come on, we're going.

30:07.540 --> 30:08.620
Hey.

30:08.620 --> 30:09.830
Hey!

30:09.830 --> 30:11.120
Don't even try it.

30:11.120 --> 30:14.290
[ Crowd murmuring ]

30:14.290 --> 30:16.500
-Don't. Let it go.
-What the hell, Sheriff?

30:16.500 --> 30:18.210
He can't just take her.
-Yeah, he can.

30:18.210 --> 30:20.670
And he better.
Right now.

30:20.670 --> 30:22.250
Come on.

30:26.420 --> 30:28.920
Everything's all right.
Everything's under control.

30:28.920 --> 30:30.040
Misunderstanding.

30:33.500 --> 30:35.380
Come on.

30:37.540 --> 30:39.120
Baker team, sound off.

30:41.750 --> 30:43.750
Baker team, sound off.

30:47.460 --> 30:49.330
Drop your weapon.

30:49.330 --> 30:51.170
I'm not gonna ask you again.

30:53.380 --> 30:55.290
Drop to the ground.

30:55.290 --> 30:56.330
[ Device beeps ]

30:56.330 --> 30:58.540
[ High-pitched screech ]
Aaaah!

30:58.540 --> 30:59.750
[ Device beeps ]

30:59.750 --> 31:02.120
High-frequency
sonic discharge.

31:02.120 --> 31:03.790
In case you were wondering.
-[ Groaning ]

31:03.790 --> 31:05.380
We can't pick up
that frequency.

31:05.380 --> 31:08.540
But an Apex?
Scrambles you up good.

31:08.540 --> 31:10.460
[ Screeching continues ]
-[ Groaning ]

31:10.460 --> 31:12.880
[ Screeching continues ]

31:12.880 --> 31:14.170
[ Screeching stops ]

31:14.170 --> 31:16.080
Welcome to
the Long Peace, swan.

31:16.080 --> 31:17.290
Ahh.

31:17.290 --> 31:18.500
Agh.

31:18.500 --> 31:21.040
Haven't seen one of you
in 10 years.

31:21.040 --> 31:23.290
Don't worry.
[ Device beeps ]

31:23.290 --> 31:24.880
[ Screeching resumes ]
-[ Groans ]

31:24.880 --> 31:27.210
...I look forward to making up
for lost time.

31:27.210 --> 31:29.710
[ Groaning ]

31:33.710 --> 31:34.710
[ Screeching ]

31:34.710 --> 31:35.710
[ Screeching stops ]

31:35.710 --> 31:37.120
How many more
are there?

31:37.120 --> 31:38.710
[ Exhales ]
I'm the only one.

31:38.710 --> 31:40.750
I don't buy that.

31:40.750 --> 31:43.670
You splash into the ocean,
survive undetected --

31:43.670 --> 31:45.960
you should be long gone --
but you stuck around. Why?

31:45.960 --> 31:47.620
Why would you stick around

31:47.620 --> 31:49.880
unless there was something
that you wanted?

31:49.880 --> 31:51.750
[ Groaning ]

31:51.750 --> 31:54.170
Or someone?

31:54.170 --> 31:57.620
And when I find out who it is
that you stuck around for,

31:57.620 --> 31:59.920
I'll put a bullet
in their head.

32:02.170 --> 32:03.250
[ Device beeps ]

32:03.250 --> 32:04.960
[ Screeching resumes ]
-[ Groaning ]

32:12.290 --> 32:17.960
♪♪

32:17.960 --> 32:24.620
♪♪

32:24.620 --> 32:26.750
Thank you.

32:32.830 --> 32:34.830
There you go, buddy.

32:38.170 --> 32:40.380
So what do you think,
Ollie?

32:40.380 --> 32:42.170
Not that bad up here,
huh?

32:46.170 --> 32:48.120
You all right?

32:50.960 --> 32:52.920
Hey. What's going on?

32:52.920 --> 32:55.670
What did I do wrong?

32:57.460 --> 32:59.460
Nothing.

32:59.460 --> 33:02.500
Then why did you
move away from me?

33:17.540 --> 33:20.580
♪♪

33:20.580 --> 33:24.960
Remember we talked about my job
being complicated?

33:24.960 --> 33:26.460
I didn't tell you
everything

33:26.460 --> 33:28.460
because I thought
you were too young,

33:28.460 --> 33:31.290
but I'm gonna tell you now...

33:31.290 --> 33:33.210
♪♪

33:33.210 --> 33:37.170
...because I don't want you
thinking for one second

33:37.170 --> 33:40.210
that any of this
is your fault. Okay?

33:44.210 --> 33:48.830
When I was a police officer
in Oakland,

33:48.830 --> 33:52.580
some people were upset
that I arrested them.

33:52.580 --> 33:58.750
And I had to leave so that they
would stop making threats.

33:58.750 --> 34:02.170
♪♪

34:02.170 --> 34:05.620
I moved away
to keep you safe,

34:05.620 --> 34:10.750
because you are the most
important thing in my life.

34:10.750 --> 34:14.500
♪♪

34:14.500 --> 34:16.420
Are you safe now?

34:16.420 --> 34:21.080
I am, and so are you
and so is your mom.

34:21.080 --> 34:23.460
♪♪

34:23.460 --> 34:25.750
Hey, you know,
you guys are gonna be

34:25.750 --> 34:27.290
moving to Portland soon.

34:27.290 --> 34:28.710
That's always been
part of the plan.

34:28.710 --> 34:30.000
Has she talked
to you about that?

34:30.000 --> 34:32.710
Okay.
Well, that's gonna happen.

34:32.710 --> 34:35.790
And then you're gonna be
like 30 minutes from me.

34:35.790 --> 34:38.120
So we can get back
on schedule

34:38.120 --> 34:40.750
of seeing each other
all the time. Okay?

34:44.670 --> 34:46.670
Hey, look at me.

34:47.960 --> 34:50.580
I love you.

34:50.580 --> 34:54.960
♪♪

34:54.960 --> 35:00.120
I will do anything for you.

35:00.120 --> 35:02.580
♪♪

35:02.580 --> 35:04.460
Anything.

35:04.460 --> 35:06.460
[ Sniffles ]

35:17.500 --> 35:22.620
♪♪

35:22.620 --> 35:27.500
♪♪

35:27.500 --> 35:33.540
♪♪

35:33.540 --> 35:36.210
[ Cellphone ringing ]

35:36.210 --> 35:38.540
Woman: HSI Field Office,
Seattle Seaport.

35:38.540 --> 35:39.880
I need information

35:39.880 --> 35:42.500
on the Tamanowas detainment
facility in Oregon, please.

35:42.500 --> 35:46.040
I'm seeing no record of any
operation under that listing.

35:46.040 --> 35:50.380
Then do a global search
of the entire Pacific Northwest.

35:50.380 --> 35:54.880
Key words -- detainment,
vetting, quarantine.

35:54.880 --> 35:58.040
I'm sorry, ma'am.
No match.

35:58.040 --> 36:02.290
I have 47 detainees
of unknown origin.

36:02.290 --> 36:04.830
I have 75
government-sanctioned staff.

36:04.830 --> 36:06.750
Ma'am, may I have
your badge number?

36:06.750 --> 36:08.580
[ Cellphone clicks ]

36:18.580 --> 36:19.920
[ Engine stops ]

36:21.790 --> 36:23.120
Why are we stopping?

36:23.120 --> 36:25.420
Oh, are you talking
to me now?

36:25.420 --> 36:27.420
And why should
I talk to you?

36:27.420 --> 36:29.620
You're taking me
against my will.

36:29.620 --> 36:32.670
I know the camp's not perfect,
but it's safe.

36:32.670 --> 36:35.330
You're protected there.

36:35.330 --> 36:38.460
Everyone at that camp --

36:38.460 --> 36:41.000
they either hate me now
or they're about to.

36:41.000 --> 36:42.460
Why?

36:44.620 --> 36:47.670
Hannah,
what's going on?

36:54.790 --> 36:56.750
Come on.

36:56.750 --> 36:58.500
Where are we going?

36:58.500 --> 37:00.710
You need to get
in the back of the truck

37:00.710 --> 37:02.500
so I can sneak you
back into the camp.

37:04.500 --> 37:06.500
No questions,
no consequences.

37:06.500 --> 37:09.040
Come on.

37:09.040 --> 37:14.380
♪♪

37:14.380 --> 37:17.750
[ Indistinct conversations ]

37:26.500 --> 37:29.040
Hey, Hannah.

37:31.250 --> 37:33.330
How's it going?

37:33.330 --> 37:36.620
What are you doing
in my cabin?

37:36.620 --> 37:39.040
[ Scoffs ] Come on.

37:39.040 --> 37:42.290
Can we get past all this
wide-eyed disbelief

37:42.290 --> 37:45.710
and just get to where we're
gonna end up eventually...

37:45.710 --> 37:46.960
Good friends.

37:46.960 --> 37:48.000
Get out.

37:48.000 --> 37:50.540
Now.

37:50.540 --> 37:51.750
I'll scream.

37:51.750 --> 37:53.920
Yeah? And then what?

37:53.920 --> 37:56.120
A bunch of people
come running over,

37:56.120 --> 37:58.580
ask what's going on,

37:58.580 --> 38:01.080
I tell them what I know.

38:01.080 --> 38:04.040
You used to be
an Apex collaborator.

38:06.670 --> 38:11.620
Maybe I'll tell it
to that big guy, Caleb.

38:11.620 --> 38:13.710
Did you see the tattoo
on his wrist?

38:13.710 --> 38:16.710
It's an Alpha-Zulu
insignia.

38:16.710 --> 38:20.380
Do you know what they used to do
to people like you?

38:22.330 --> 38:24.000
Horrible stuff.

38:24.000 --> 38:25.620
Don't touch me.

38:28.170 --> 38:30.080
[ Gasps ] Ahh.

38:31.380 --> 38:33.830
You don't seem to get it.

38:35.170 --> 38:40.790
While you're in here,
I own you.

38:40.790 --> 38:42.120
[ Breathing shakily ]

38:47.080 --> 38:48.920
[ Door opens ]

38:50.210 --> 38:52.040
[ Door closes ]

38:57.580 --> 39:02.380
♪♪

39:02.380 --> 39:06.830
♪♪

39:06.830 --> 39:11.500
♪♪

39:11.500 --> 39:16.170
♪♪

39:16.170 --> 39:19.040
No one has ever
survived Mantle's.

39:19.040 --> 39:21.120
No is immune.

39:22.620 --> 39:25.120
No one except...

39:25.120 --> 39:26.960
Apex.

39:26.960 --> 39:29.460
What is Apex?

39:29.460 --> 39:34.000
♪♪

39:34.000 --> 39:38.580
♪♪

39:38.580 --> 39:44.000
♪♪

39:45.380 --> 39:47.500
Yeah!

39:47.500 --> 39:49.170
[ Crowd cheering ]

39:49.170 --> 39:50.750
Yeah.

39:52.380 --> 39:54.670
Oh!

39:54.670 --> 40:01.620
♪♪

40:03.250 --> 40:05.460
There it is!
[ Chuckles ]

40:11.330 --> 40:12.960
[ Glass shatters ]

40:12.960 --> 40:14.750
Dad, what was that?

40:14.750 --> 40:16.790
You stay right here, okay?
I won't be long.

40:18.960 --> 40:20.380
[ Woman screaming ]

40:20.380 --> 40:21.830
[ Car alarm blaring ]
What's going on?

40:21.830 --> 40:23.710
Watch out. Back it up.

40:23.710 --> 40:25.380
Back it up!

40:25.380 --> 40:27.170
[ Blaring continues ]

40:42.540 --> 40:44.670
[ Blaring continues ]

40:52.500 --> 40:54.420
Oliver!

40:54.420 --> 40:56.210
Ollie!

40:56.210 --> 41:01.500
♪♪

41:01.500 --> 41:07.710
♪♪

41:07.710 --> 41:10.330
Oliver!

41:10.330 --> 41:16.330
♪♪

41:16.330 --> 41:22.330
♪♪

41:22.330 --> 41:28.330
♪♪

41:28.330 --> 41:34.330
♪♪

41:34.330 --> 41:40.290
♪♪

